# Local Bazel overrides ‚Äî copy to `.bazelrc.user` (gitignored) and edit.
#
# `.bazelrc` try-imports `.bazelrc.user` last, so anything here wins over the
# committed config. Use it for environment-specific values that shouldn't be
# checked in ‚Äî most commonly the RBE endpoint for `--config=remote`.
#
# Example: point `--config=remote` at a Buildbarn cluster you can reach
# (e.g. the lab cluster over Tailscale). The endpoint is plaintext gRPC because
# the transport (WireGuard/Tailscale) already encrypts it.
#
#   build:remote --remote_executor=grpc://bb.example.internal:8980
#   build:remote --remote_instance_name=
#
# Then:  bazel build --config=remote //...
#
# Optionally report invocations to a BES backend (e.g. bb-portal / BuildBuddy)
# for a browsable build UI:
#
#   build --bes_backend=grpc://bb-portal.example.internal:8082    # gRPC, not https
#   build --bes_results_url=https://bb-portal.example.internal/bazel-invocations/
#
# The `remote_platform` exec_properties in //tools/remote-toolchains must match
# the queue the cluster's scheduler advertises, or actions queue with no worker.
